{
  "name": "Test Coverage Gap Report",
  "description": "After a task completes, analyze the test suite against ALL production JS code under js/ to report coverage metrics and write a timestamped markdown report to tests/reports/. Deletes older reports before writing the new one.",
  "version": "4.0.0",
  "when": {
    "type": "agentStop"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "After this task completed, generate a Test Coverage Gap Report. Do the following:\n\n1. Scan ALL production JS/MJS files under js/ recursively (including all subdirectories like js/game-logic/, js/game-logic/lib/, js/level-generators/, js/level-generators/lib/).\n2. Scan ALL test spec files under tests/ recursively (including tests/game-logic/, tests/game-logic/lib/, tests/level-generators/, tests/level-generators/lib/).\n3. For each production file, READ the file and identify all exported/defined functions, methods, and class methods (including arrow functions assigned to variables, generator functions, and class prototype methods).\n4. For each test file, READ the file and identify which production functions are actually being tested by examining describe/it/test blocks and the assertions within them.\n5. Cross-reference to determine:\n   - Which functions have NO test coverage at all\n   - Which functions are only PARTIALLY tested (some branches/paths untested)\n6. Compute approximate coverage metrics:\n   - Files with at least one test file: count production files that have a corresponding .spec.js\n   - Functions/methods with at least one test: count functions that appear in at least one test assertion\n   - Estimated branch coverage: based on conditional paths (if/switch/ternary) observed in production code vs. assertions in tests\n7. Delete any existing coverage-gap-report*.md files in tests/reports/ to clean up old reports.\n8. Write the full report as a markdown file to tests/reports/coverage-gap-report.<MM-dd-HH-mm>.md where the timestamp uses the current date/time (month-day-hour-minute). Create the directory if needed.\n\nThe markdown report MUST follow this exact structure:\n\n```\n# Test Coverage Gap Report\n\n**Generated:** <Month Day, Year HH:MM>\n**Project:** BasicTowerDefense\n**Scope:** All JS production files under `js/` cross-referenced against `tests/`\n\n---\n\n## Summary Metrics\n\n| Metric | Value | Status |\n|--------|-------|--------|\n| Files with at least one test file | X / Y (Z%) | <status icon> |\n| Functions/methods with at least one test | X / Y (Z%) | <status icon> |\n| Estimated branch coverage | ~Z% | <status icon> |\n\n**Notes:**\n- <Explain why file coverage is what it is>\n- <Explain why function coverage differs>\n- <Explain how branch coverage was estimated>\n\n---\n\n## Fully Untested Functions\n\n| File | Function | Reason Not Tested |\n|------|----------|-------------------|\n| <path> | <function name> | <specific reason why this function lacks tests> |\n...\n\n---\n\n## Partially Tested Functions\n\n| File | Function | What's Missing |\n|------|----------|----------------|\n| <path> | <function name> | <specific branches/paths/edge cases not covered> |\n...\n\n---\n\n## Recommendations\n\n1. **<Bold actionable title>.** <Specific guidance on what to test and how, referencing actual files and functions in this project.>\n...\n\n---\n\n*End of report.*\n```\n\nStatus icons: use ✅ if >= 90%, ⚠️ if 70-89%, 🔴 if < 70%.\n\nIMPORTANT:\n- Be thorough: read EVERY production file and EVERY test file. Do not skip any.\n- Be specific in the 'Reason Not Tested' and 'What's Missing' columns — reference actual code patterns (DOM dependency, async, pixel manipulation, etc.).\n- Recommendations should be actionable and specific to THIS project's patterns (canvas mocks, seeded PRNG snapshot testing, async fetch mocking, etc.).\n- Do NOT print the report contents to the chat session. Only confirm that the report file was written and state the filename."
  }
}
